archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.name: Business Reference Model (copy)
archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation: The poster summarises the Business Reference Model. It shows value chains for higher education, and the business capabilities that enable them. V2.0.1

children.content: The Higher Education Business Reference Model descripbes a standard set of Business Architecture elements relevat to Higher Education. It can be used as a refernce for Business Stakeholders, Enterprise Architects, and Technology Strategists to engage in discussion regarding business effectivenesss, needs and challenges. The primary attribute of the Business Reference Model is the embedded capability model, which elaborates the core value chains for higher education and the underlying business capabilities.
